{
  "texts": [
    "In the medical field, different medical institutions and professionals may use different terms to describe the same or similar clinical diagnoses, which can cause difficulties and misunderstandings in data exchange, statistics, and analysis.",
    "Therefore, standardizing clinical diagnostic terms is an important task.",
    "The standardized terms can be used to unify treatment plans and disease statistics, as well as to build clinical diagnostic knowledge bases.",
    "The data in our study were clustered into 107 clusters, and each cluster was analyzed separately, resulting in a diagnostic clustering table.",
    "Part of the results of the clustering table are shown in Table 2."
  ]
}